%NUMBER :+
   Use%NUMBER+to turn NUMBER mode on or off ("ON" is the default) and to
   indicate whether you want standard numbering, COBOL numbering, or bot
   ("STD" is the default). When NUMBER mode is set on, edit creates an
   ascending sequence number for any records that do not already contain

   More topic will be presented in the EDIT tutorial.
+
+Enter%&EPF+to exit the tutorial and return to the EDIT modes control pa
+Hit%ENTER+to go on to the next tutorial panel
)INIT
  &EPF = PFK(END)
  IF (&EPF = &Z)
    &EPF = 'END'
  &D = TRUNC(&EPF,2)
  &DT = .TRAIL
  &D = TRUNC(&DT,1)
  IF (&D = '0')
    &DT = .TRAIL
    &EPF = 'PF&DT'
)PROC
)END
